"a.谨慎的，小心翼翼的 【英】 adj. 谨慎的，小心翼翼的( looking out for danger) 【考】 wary : gulled / vigilant : ambushed / exacting : satisfied(谨慎的不易被骗/警 觉的不易中埋伏/苛刻 的不易满足) 【例】 She was wary of strangers. adj. 谨慎的; 小心翼翼的 【记】war, y: 在战斗中要小心翼翼的, 不然就歇菜了. 【类】wary: gulled[duped] = exacting: satisfied = vigilant: ambushed[entrapped, waylaid]谨慎的不易被骗 = 挑剔的不易被满足 = 警觉的不易中埋伏 【反】remiss(adj 玩忽职守的) 【记】源自aware 意识到的，警惕的；worry 担心，烦恼 wary (adj.)  late 15c., with -y (2) + ware, from Old English wær ""prudent, aware, alert, wary,"" from Proto-Germanic *waraz (cognates: Old Norse varr ""attentive,"" Gothic wars ""cautious,"" Old Saxon giwar, Middle Dutch gheware, Old High German giwar, German gewahr ""aware""), from PIE root *wer- (4) ""to perceive, watch out for"" (see ward (n.)). Related: Warily; wariness."
